========================

\_A sandbox to test units against each other\_

This scene is for testing the design of RTS units. Units can be assembled from prefabs of parts. Components for sensors and behaviours can be added. Part categories include weapons (such as lasers and missiles) and movement systems (like wheels, treads, or propellers).

Game designers will create unit designs from the parts and components, and then place armies of these units in the scene. Units assigned to different teams will fight each other. The game designers will use this to test out new ideas for unit parts and to balance the units.

Eventually we'd like to release a game that combines the factory automation and RTS genres and allows players to assemble custom unit designs from parts, using conveyor belts and assemblers.

File descriptions
========================

## Behaviours
\* UnitBehaviour.cs - Base class for behaviours. Units can have multiple behaviours. Behaviours can be ordered in the editor and they will run in this order. Later behaviours can override actions from earlier behaviours.
\* SeekAndDestroy.cs - This behaviour causes a unit to patrol the area for enemies and attack any enemies found on sight.
\* Flee.cs - Makes the unit flee from battle. You can set it to only flee when low on health.

## Parts
\* UnitPart.cs - Base class for parts. Currently has `weight` and provides a reference to the Unit for convenience. Will probably handle sockets as well.
\* Armor.cs - you can add this component to any part or unit. It will give the unit more hit points.
\* BasicGun.cs - A gun component. Add as part of a gun prefab to make it shoot. You can set properties of the gun such as the damage, cooldown and range.
\* BasicMovement.cs - A movement component. Parts with this component allow the unit to move. You can set properties such as the acceleration, top speed, turning radius, etc.

## Sensors
\* Vision.cs - A component that lets the unit detect other units. It sees in a cone in front of the unit.

## Designs
\* Peewee - A basic infantry unit with a gun.
\* Turret - A stationary, defensive unit with two cannons.

## Other files
\* UnitManager.cs
\* Unit.cs
\* HealthBar.cs

## Interfaces
\* IPosition - Anything that has a position. It contains a `Vector3 Position { get; }` property.
\* ITargetable - An interface for things that can be targeted, such as units, buildings, or even locations on the map.
\* IWeapon - An interface for weapons, such as BasicGun. You can call `SetTarget(ITargetable target)` to set a target for the weapon. The weapon should keep attacking that target automatically until it can't anymore or a new target is set.
\* IMovement - An interface for movement components, such as BasicMovement. You an call `SetTarget(ITargetable target, float proximity = 0.5f)` to tell it where to move to. The movement component should automatically move to within `proximity` meters of the target. If the target is a unit, it should follow the unit.
\* ISensor - For components that detects units.
\* IHealth - Something that has hit points, like a unit or building.
Possible future features
========================
(A lot of these were suggested by ChatGPT)

## Behaviours
\* DefendArea.cs: A behavior that makes the unit defend a specific area, engaging enemies that come too close.
\* RepairAndSupport.cs: A behavior that enables the unit to repair or support friendly units within a defined radius.

## Parts
\* Shield.cs: A component that provides a regenerating energy shield to the unit, which can absorb a certain amount of damage before the armor or hit points are affected.
\* StealthSystem.cs: A part that allows the unit to become invisible or difficult to detect by enemy sensors.
\* ArtilleryWeapon.cs: A long-range weapon component with customizable attributes, such as projectile type, range, and splash damage.

## Sensors
\* Radar.cs: A component that can detect cloaked units.

## Designs
\* Scout: A fast-moving unit with enhanced sensors for reconnaissance and intel gathering.
\* Engineer: A support unit that can repair, build, or upgrade other units and structures.
\* HeavyAssault: A heavily armored unit with multiple weapon systems for dealing with various types of enemy units.

## Utility classes
\* FormationManager.cs: A system for managing unit formations, allowing the player to create and modify formations for better control of their units.
\* DynamicObstacles.cs: A script that enables the creation of dynamic obstacles, such as destructible terrain or moving hazards, to add complexity and challenge to the sandbox.

## UI
\* UnitSelectionUI.cs: A user interface for selecting and controlling individual units or groups of units.
\* UnitInfoPanel.cs: A panel that displays detailed information about a selected unit, including its current parts, sensors, and behaviors.
\* DesignBlueprintUI.cs: A user interface that allows the player to create, save, and load custom unit designs using available parts, sensors, and behaviors.

